org.cruk.genologics.api.debugging

Class HttpClientTimingAspect

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cruk.genologics.api.debugging.HttpClientTimingAspect

  • public class HttpClientTimingAspect
extends Object
    Testing aspect that reports on the calls being made by the HTTP client talking to the Genologics API. Reports on the URI being called and the time the call took to execute.

      • timeCall

        public Object timeCall(ProceedingJoinPoint pjp)
                throws Throwable
        Join point that, if the logging is set to DEBUG, will report on the call made with the HttpClient and the time taken to get a response.
        Parameters:
        pjp - The AspectJ join point object. One of the arguments in this object must be the HttpMethod being invoked.
        Returns:
        The result of proceeding with the join point.
        Throws:
        Throwable - if there is any failure.
        See Also:
        HttpClient.execute(HttpUriRequest)
